As manager of your new power plant, you must now hire an assistant manager.
The assistant manager is the head of day to day operations and will be the
one responsible for handling any important events that may happen during the
Work week. An Assistant manager has 4 key traits that allow them to be
successful at their job. Their Public Relations ability is very important to 
deal with customers and city folk. Their staff management ability to deal with
crew members both in that plant and out in the field. Their Investment Ability
to allocate funds properly to certain areas of the plant. Finally their Plant
Maintenance ability to keep the plant running as efficiently as possible. 
Chose wisely one of the managers below.
